Marcelo Antonio Ramrez Gormaz (born May 29, 1965) is a retired Chilean football goalkeeper. He who was capped 37 times for the Chilean national team between 1993 and 2001, and was an unused substitute player for the 1998 FIFA World Cup. Ramrez is described as a late bloomer who was quick off the line and experienced success at saving penalty kicks. 
